tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE weather_data (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  date DATE,
  temperature REAL,
  precipitation REAL
)

CREATE TABLE WeatherData (
    location_id INT,
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE WeatherData (
    date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    PRIMARY KEY (date, location)
)

CREATE TABLE EnergyGeneration (
    date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    solar_generation FLOAT,
    wind_generation FLOAT,
    hydro_generation FLOAT,
    PRIMARY KEY (date, location)
)

CREATE TABLE ForecastData (
    date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    weather_condition VARCHAR(50),
    energy_forecast FLOAT,
    PRIMARY KEY (date, location)
)

CREATE TABLE UtilizationData (
    date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(50),
    energy_utilization FLOAT,
    optimization_strategy VARCHAR(50),
    PRIMARY KEY (date, location)
)

CREATE TABLE weather_data (
  date DATE,
  temperature INT,
  humidity INT,
  wind_speed INT,
  solar_radiation INT
);

CREATE TABLE location (
  location_id INT,
  city VARCHAR(50),
  country VARCHAR(50),
  latitude DECIMAL(10, 8),
  longitude DECIMAL(11, 8)
);
